make the following slightly emotional;
{7.	Overwhelming fatigue and tiredness with little to no energy even after rest and sleep, wanting to sleep again, then sets in.  These physical symptoms of emotional distress have compounded my overall sense of despair, helplessness and deepens my depression.
8.	Debilitating exhaustion that affects my breathing rhythm pattern and rate and doing physical tasks like walking, is worsening my feelings of despair and helplessness. 
9.	Having difficulties in thinking and concentrating and focusing on tasks. This mental fog keeps obstructing my ability to function and perform tasks, no matter how small or minor. Causing also, increased racing heartbeats, sweating and increased discomfort with feelings of embarrassment, not wanting to be with anyone, wanting to run away and feeling isolated. 
10.	Much of my symptoms and conditions change quickly and unpredictably, deteriorating my mental and emotional state rapidly through seemingly insignificant triggers. This constant instability has created a battle with myself, a daily struggle to survive to maintain my well-being, to prevent me, more pain and suffering. My focus is merely on surviving each day.}
